			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hail fellow monks<BR>
<BR>
To the one up top, I will my part of wisdom.<BR>
<BR>
At lvl 6 xp in Freeport was starting to slow me down. I got lvl 7, but it took me a while. I almost got to lvl 7, but figured, to heck with it. SO I got one of those ever-so-helpful wizzies to port me to tox, then take me to erudin, then hopped on the boat to Qeynos.<BR>
<BR>
From there, I went to Blackburrow. I got lvl 8 in just a little while, lvl 9 was a blast, lvl 10 was slightly harder, but so little I hardly noticed. I'm now 11, getting a half a blue bubble from every giant snake I fight. And they all con blue!<BR>
<BR>
Now, for the debate between iksars and humans. I agree with the person who was completely blunt. As I don't get to play often, the xp bonus makes life easier. Plus, humans hit for harder and faster! So the iksar regen doesn't do much good, because with humans, your enemy is already a bleeding corpse on the ground!<BR>
<BR>
I also agree heavily with &quot; A buffed monk is a dangerous monk&quot; Try and get skin like nature, maybe a few synbols as well. As well as agility, dex and str buffs.<BR>
<BR>
Caedil<BR>
Monk of the Ashen Order<BR>
11th season<BR>
The Seventh Hammer<BR>
