	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I started in freeport &amp; stayed there till i got my kick. Then just jump on the boat &amp; head to Greater Faydark. Find the Orc Hill and start kicking butt with or without a group. with a group just means less down time.Soon as you reach lvl 8 start making trips to Crushbone and attack every centurion in sight to get the CB Belts. At this level avoid legionnaires like they have the plague, even if u are in a group. Crushbone is a very good level as long as u keep an eye out for trains, they can pose a danger all the way to lvl 20. Start with centurions, then Slaver's, Lego's, Emmi's, Oracle's, even Emperor crush himself. The big plus is that every CB Belt &amp; every 2 Lego Pads is trade able for either hard cash from other players or exp in kaladim (see canloe in south kaladim). Pop back to freeport when u get a new skill but only put 1 pt into them save the rest for feign death. This is a fast fun way to lvl just as long as u remember to watch out for the trains.
				</font>
			</td>

