	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok... whenever i see a high level monk he (never have seen a high level she actually) always is using 1hb weapons. The thing is that my fists consistently do more damage than any of the 1hb weapons available to me. What i did was purchase a survival staff (humans could just loot a splintering club, pretty much the same thing), max my 1hb when I level up, and put it in the bank until i level up again. This way you don't get to level twenty-something and decide it's time to train a weapon skill from scratch(a very painful process).<BR>
<BR>
 I play an iksar monk mainly because i started a human ranger once and i couldn't stand not being able to see at night. Besides, regen, foraging, swimming(yes, the water is my friend), and infravision are well worth the exp penalty (which i haven't noticed yet; i've been leveling so darn fast). And Kunark is so much prettier to start a character in compared to quenos (blah) or freeport (ugh).<BR>
<BR>
But hey, i'm not the only one who thinks that humans suck, just ask the Irontoe brigade.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
